Good Class Bungalow
Botanic Gardens-Cluny Vicinity Singapore

Nestled a stone’s throw away from the UNESCO WorldHeritage-listed Singapore Botanic Gardens and just a fewminutes' drive to the Orchard Road shopping belt and the Central Business District, this residence offers a serene environment seamlessly blending the beauty of nature with urban convenience.

The facade’s stately aesthetics are complemented by well-manicured hedges, providing an oasis of tranquility. The layout ensures privacy and offers an extraordinary living experience with grandeur and architectural finesse.

title: LEONIE HILL RESIDENCES, 1 Leonie Hill Rd, Singapore 239191
description:
Leonie Hill Residences is a freehold apartment completed in 2005. It is located along Leonie Hill Road in River Valley, in District 9. It is accessible through the nearest MRTs including Great World TE15 and Orchard TE14, NS22. The nearest schools are ERC Institute and River Valley Primary School.

Most people are attracted to District 9, as it has a huge selection of exclusive cosmopolitan bistros and on the other end of the scale, a number of popular international fast food restaurants. Located near Orchard Road, ION Orchard Mall is home to designer brands, and represents one of Singapore’s best retail, dining and entertainment boulevards, catering to any taste or budget and ranging from luxury brands to high street fashion.

title: Cubik - Penthouse 2+1 with Attic and Private Pool, LORONG K TELOK KURAU
description:
A blend of modernity and luxury. Clean sleek lines with cutting-edge design, with 20 apartments and 4 exclusive penthouse units, discover a truly sophisticated lifestyle at Cubik.

Within walking distance, enjoy quiet evenings at the Telok Kurau Park which has easy access via Siglap Park Connector to Kembangan MRT station and East Coast Park. Find leisure at the East Coast Recreation Centre, food paradise at Siglap and Katong eateries and fulfil your shopping needs at Parkway Parade.

Cubik is also within 2km from elite schools such as Tao Nan School, CHIJ, Victoria Junior College. Only minutes away from major expressways, and easy access to the commercial and entertainment attractions of the city.

title: ALTEZ, ENGGOR STREET
description:
At a staggering 250 metres, Altez brings a new perspective to the term “high-life”. The 62-storey development offers panoramic views of the sea and the city, and full condominium facilities. Just two minutes’ walk from Tanjong Pagar MRT Station, residents enjoy excellent access to the Central Business District and the Marina Coastal Expressway (MCE).

URA Draft Master Plan 2019 highlighted the Downtown transformation plan and The Greater Southern Waterfront development plan. Strategically located at downtown Tanjong Pagar, Altez is well-positioned to benefit from the enlivening enhancements of both zones. The Downtown transformation plan focuses on the various needs of modern lifestyles, increasing conveniences and connectivity to create a vibrant place for the modern working professional to live and work in. The Greater Southern Waterfront development plan spans across 2,000 hectares from Gardens by the Bay East to Pasir Panjang. It promises an attractive waterfront promenade where various places of interests, like the historic Tanjong Pagar Railway, would be connected. The development is also directly linked to Icon Village, a destination mall designed to create a cosmopolitan lifestyle, and a short walk away from 100 AM retail mall.

Winner of Asia Pacific Property Award 2015, Five-Star, Residential (High-Rise) Architecture Singapore
Winner of Singapore Good Design Award 2015, SG Mark
Winner of MIPIM Asia Awards 2015, Silver, Best Residential Development

Amenities
- Directly linked to Icon Village mall
- 2 minutes’ walk to Tanjong Pagar MRT Station
- Easy access to Marina Coastal Expressway (MCE)

title: PARKSUITES, HOLLAND GROVE ROAD
description:
A home inspired by the park-scape, Parksuites is designed to be intimate, and will fit right in to the close-knit community that has formed in this charming locale. Enjoy more than just sweeping views of the greens; surround yourself with spaces that open up to nature. It is Henry Park reinterpreted. It is SOHO living like you’ve never seen before.
 
At Parksuites, discover a residential development integrated with artisanal retail and F&B options. Shop and dine amidst the cool and welcoming greenery of Henry Park with the comforts of home steps away. Truly, a unique setting like no other.
 
Situated along Holland Grove Road and the tranquil neighbourhood of Mount Sinai, Parksuites offers you a location that brings the world nearer to you. Henry Park Primary School, a renowned GEP school, is located within 1 kilometre of Parksuites.
 
Residents can enjoy greater convenience with complimentary shuttle bus service from Parksuites to Holland Village and Buona Vista MRT Stations.*

For the action buffs, Savannah CondoPark includes two tennis courts, while an assortment of pools add refreshing splashed of azure blue amidst the natural foliage. Gracing the edge of the central pool is the Peninsula Pool Deck that represents an ideal spot for quiet meditation or indulgent sun bathing.

Savannah CondoPark is accessible via major transport networks such as the Pan Island Expressway (PIE), Tampines Expressway (TPE) and East Coast Parkway (ECP). Nearby shopping malls are the Eastpoint Mall, Century Square, Tampines Mall. It is located near Upper Changi MRT and Tampines East MRT

title: BIJOU, JALAN MAT JAMBOL
description:
Bijou, a freehold development where sophisticated living transcends into an expression of one's individuality. Experience downtown’s dynamism along the fringes of Singapore’s CBD. This Far East SOHO development perfectly balances urban appeal with classical garden landscapes encircling a rooftop pool and gym.

During National Day Rally 2019, the Singapore Government highlighted on the future transformation plans for Greater Southern Waterfront as part of nation building.

Stretching across 2,000 hectares of land from Pasir Panjang to Gardens by the Bay East, this redevelopment would include a business district, 30-km long scenic waterfront promenade, a green corridor linking Labrador Park to Gardens by the Bay and the development of Pulau Brani into a new tourism attraction – reshaping Greater Southern Waterfront as a new ‘live, work and play’ precinct.

Strategically situated in a tranquil spot directly opposite Pasir Panjang MRT Station, Bijou is in close proximity to key business hubs such as Mapletree Business City and also retail and recreational venues. Come 2025, Bijou will enjoy added connectivity to the CBD with the completion of the Circle Line loop.

Woven ingeniously throughout the grounds, the facilities provide for your endless indulgence: socialising in the clubhouse, working out in the gym, splashing in the myriad pools, or retreating to the Principal Sky Club where you can dream with your head in the clouds. Furnished with a wine cellar for residents’ private use, as well as an entertainment suite, function room, wet and dry kitchens, and outdoor dining facilities, the clubhouse is an elegant social space for relaxing an entertaining that can also be reserved for private parties.

A peaceful haven high above the city, the 24th storey Principal Sky Club features a pool, private Jacuzzi and private dining pavilion, framed by soaring bird’s eye views.

title: PARC CLEMATIS, Jln Lempeng, Singapore
description: An Awards winning development strategically located in the matured estate of Clementi, surrounded by abundance of amenities. The location is perfect for those looking to enjoy the vibrancy of the city yet at the same offers the enjoyment of nature for those who wish to escape from the city life. In addition, all the tower blocks in Parc Clematis are tilted in north-south facing orientation to avoid direct west sunrays. It was purposely built with space between tower blocks to create distance for better privacy between all the units. With this design, more greeneries are planted at the base of the blocks to give a see-through vantage views towards landscape area while allowing more sunlight and airflow through the neighbourhood. Moreover, Parc Clematis also offer a wide variety of facilities for its residents such as 50-meter pool, reflexology garden, aquatherapy / hydrotherapy pool, indoor gymnasium, multipurpose court and many more.

The house extends from the dining room to the outdoor for alfresco entertainment and perfect for stand up parties in the garden, BBQ under the stars or a dip in the pool on a sunny day and sun bath in the comfort and privacy of your home. Equally perfect for families with children to run or play on the trampoline. The second level comes with 5 functional and regular sized bedrooms and bathrooms. The house comes with helper’s quarters.

Your every need is catered to with this home's central location. Enjoy effortless access to the diverse offerings of Holland Village, Jelita Shopping Centre, and Guthrie House, or find solace in the natural beauty of the Botanic Gardens and Bukit Timah Hill.

description:

title: THE PEAK, PEPYS ROAD
description:
Nestled atop the tranquil hilltops of Pepys Road, The Peak epitomises both exclusivity and seamless connectivity. This development is characterised by its low-density living, offering residents unparalleled privacy and tranquility amidst the bustling city.

The Peak is a haven for those seeking a serene retreat into nature with Kent Ridge Park right at its doorstep.

Strategically located, The Peak is a mere 15-minute drive from the Central Business District and Marina Bay Financial Centre. Additionally, VivoCity, Singapore's largest shopping mall, is just a 9-minute drive away, offering a plethora of retail, dining, and entertainment options.

The development's proximity to Singapore's dynamic Technology Corridor, including one-north and the Dover Knowledge District, positions it at the heart of innovation and commerce.

Surrounded by educational institutions such as United World College (Dover), Nexus International School, Tanglin Trust School, Nan Hua High School, Anglo-Chinese School (Independent), and National University of Singapore, The Peak is an ideal choice for families and professionals seeking a balanced and enriching lifestyle.

title: MARINA BAY RESIDENCES, MARINA BOULEVARD
description:
Set in the heart of the Marina Bay district, Marina Bay Residences offers residents a superb selection of business and pleasure activities. The Marina Bay Financial Centre is right next door and the corporate and business centre of Raffles Place is less than a five minute stroll away. With Marina Bay Sands integrated resort and the Esplanade just across the Bay, Marina Bay Residences is the ultimate location for live, work and play.

Marina Bay Area, a symbol of Singapore's transformation into a global financial and entertainment hub. This district showcases cutting-edge architecture, state-of-the-art facilities, and breathtaking views.

Marina Bay Sands is one of the most iconic landmarks in this area. The integrated resort complex is known for its stunning architecture, which includes the famous rooftop Skypark that offers panoramic views of the city. Inside, you'll find a casino, luxury shopping, and numerous fine-dining options.

The Marina Bay area is also home to Gardens by the Bay, an award-winning garden featuring the iconic Supertree Grove, Cloud Forest, and Flower Dome. These futuristic gardens are both a botanical wonder and a testament to Singapore's commitment to sustainable urban development.

Marina Bay is also a cultural hub with institutions like the ArtScience Museum, which hosts fascinating exhibitions that explore the intersection of art and science. The Esplanade – Theatres on the Bay is another architectural gem and a hub for the performing arts.
The area comes alive at night when the Marina Bay Sands Light and Water Show dazzles spectators with its synchronised music, water, and light performance. The Helix Bridge, shaped like a DNA molecule, is another architectural wonder that lights up beautifully in the evening.

Residents enjoy a privileged location that invites them to experience the beauty of Marina Bay in all its glory. It is within walking distance of Singapore's most iconic landmarks, including the Marina Bay Sands, Gardens by the Bay, and the bustling Central Business District, making it a perfect choice for both leisure and business.

title: EDEN RESIDENCES CAPITOL, STAMFORD ROAD
description:
The centrepiece of an iconic integrated development comprising three landmarks – Stamford House, Capitol Building and Capitol Theatre. Located in the Civic District, perched above Singapore’s well-known historical street corner, the curved residential block offers a front row seat to the city’s Civic and Cultural District as well as spectacular views of Marina Bay and beyond.

Eden Residences Capitol is a luxurious residential edifice that sits across the road from The City Hall MRT Interchange and is literally a stone’s throw away to Peninsula Plaza and Raffles City. Living in the Eden Residences Capitol provides an easy access to the fitness and recreational parks like that of Fort Canning Park. Residents can also enjoy the convenience of the amenities nearby such as banks, supermarket, retails outlets, restaurants and other necessities.
